TITLE: DC suspect wanted for armed hijacking of ambulance as EMS treated patient
SUMMARY: The DC Metro Police Department is seeking the identity of a man accused of displaying a handgun and threatening EMS personnel before making off with an ambulance Saturday.

TITLE: NYC corrections captain at Rikers dies in Dominican Republic after Brazilian butt lift from bogus doc: report
SUMMARY: A 49-year-old New York City Corrections Captain at Rikers Island died in the Dominican Republic after receiving Brazilian butt lift surgery from infamous Dr. Hector Cabral.

TITLE: Missouri firefighters rescue 7 people trapped up to 40 feet in air on carnival ride
SUMMARY: Firefighters in Kirkwood, Missouri, rescued seven passengers who were trapped on a carnival ride during a fundraising event for a local Catholic church on Friday night.

TITLE: Chattanooga shooting leaves 3 dead and 14 injured, some struck by fleeing cars
SUMMARY: A shooting in downtown Chattanooga has left three dead and 14 injured, with some of the injuries coming when bystanders were struck by the suspects fleeing vehicle.

TITLE: Tropical Storm Alex heads toward Bermuda with high winds
SUMMARY: Tropical Storm Alex moved toward Bermuda Sunday, prompting tropical storm warnings in the area after passing Florida as the first Atlantic hurricane of the season.

TITLE: Philadelphia mayor responds to mass shooting that left 3 dead, 11 wounded; suspects still at large
SUMMARY: Philadelphia Democratic Mayor Jim Kenney issued a statement responding to a mass shooting that killed three and wounded 11 others Saturday. The suspects still remain at large.

TITLE: Pizza Hut facing boycott calls after promoting 'drag kids' book for kindergartners
SUMMARY: Pizza Hut is facing boycott calls after promoting a book for kids as young as pre-K that "celebrates drag kids" for the company's  "Book It!" reading incentive program.

TITLE: Utah teen tackles potential armed robber at restaurant, police say
SUMMARY: A 17-year-old employee at Durango's Mexican Grill in St. George, Utah, tackled a potentially armed suspect during an attempted robbery on Friday night, authorities said.

TITLE: Notre Dame changes fight song to include 'daughters' in the lyrics
SUMMARY: The University of Notre Dame is changing the lyrics to its fight song for the first time in almost 100 years, adding the word 'daughters' to celebrate the school's women.

TITLE: Wisconsin judge's alleged killer identified; Whitmer, McConnell, Evers among 13 names on hitlist: report
SUMMARY: Wisconsin's Department of Justice identified the suspect gunman as Douglas K. Uhde, accused of killing retired Judge John Roemer and having a hitlist of other political targets.

TITLE: Top Gun Maverick: Navy, Air Force look for recruitment boost following big opening for Tom Cruise sequel
SUMMARY: The original "Top Gun" famously boosted Naval Aviator recruitment by about 500%, and officials believe the new sequel can have a similar effect on current recruitment efforts.

TITLE: Chicago man charged with shooting US marshal, police dog
SUMMARY: Tarrion Johnson, 19, was arrested after he allegedly wounded a U.S. Marshal and his police dog during a shooting Thursday afternoon on Chicago's Northwest Side.

TITLE: Chicago suburb police officer shoots, kills hatchet wielding man who pulled up during traffic stop
SUMMARY: A police officer in the Chicago suburb of Naperville, Illinois, shot and killed a man who authorities say was depicted in bodycam footage charging at the cop with a hatchet.

TITLE: CBP makes massive cocaine bust in Puerto Rico
SUMMARY: U.S. Customs and Border Protection agents seized hundreds of pounds of cocaine and arrested three suspects in a massive bust off the coast of Puerto Rico this week.

TITLE: Philadelphia mass shooting on South Street leaves 3 dead, about a dozen injured
SUMMARY: At least three people are dead in Philadelphia following a mass shooting incident. Police responded to the scene just after midnight.

TITLE: Uvalde, Texas school shooting response hampered by poor police radio communications: official
SUMMARY: The cops who waited inside a Texas school while a mass shooter was barricaded in a classroom could only receive sporadic and unreliable radio communications.

TITLE: Mayor Eric Adams applauds NYPD over handling of suspect accused of killing food delivery man
SUMMARY: New York City Mayor Adams praised the NYPD’s thoroughness in ensuring the right person was arrested for the murder of a Chinese food delivery man.

TITLE: California woman finds $36K in cash hidden inside couch acquired through Craigslist
SUMMARY: A California woman found a huge sum of cash in a couch that she picked up for free on Craigslist. Thinking it may be a gimmick, she called the family.

TITLE: Michigan suspect blames 'demonic control' after allegedly killing girl on beach
SUMMARY: A Michigan man claimed that he was under "demonic control" when he allegedly killed a 12-year-old girl and critically injured her older sister.

TITLE: Texas community holds vigil for family allegedly murdered by escaped inmate
SUMMARY: Leon County, Texas community members came together for a vigil in remembrance of the family that was allegedly killed by an escaped prison inmate.
